RACE.RACE_TEXT: TURF PARADISE RACE 3 1M Dirt CR: 77. Claiming Purse 12400. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since February 15 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $8,500. Arizona Bred Claiming Price $10, 000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LADY LANA sprinted clear at once, raced four-wide while setting the pace, responded when challenged by VALUE DANCER nearing the three-eighths marker, vied with that rival and drew off through the final furlong with complete authority. VALUE DANCER chased the winner while racing five-wide, moved up to engage nearing the three-eighths pole, vied but could not match strides with that foe in the drive. FAST TO FORTUNE lagged early, raced five-wide through the second turn and was eased through the lane. THE RACE WAS HAND TIMED. SEVEN-EIGHTHS TIME CHANGED UPON REVIEW.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TURF PARADISE RACE 4 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 69. Maiden Claiming Purse 9400. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $4,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: K P HARRY KITTY was reserved just off the leaders early, moved four-wide through the turn, angled out further into the lane, reached the fore with a sixteenth to run and drew off. DADDY'SFAVORITESON settled off the leaders early, moved five-wide through the turn and finished with a steady rally. ANGRY EMMY broke sharply to duel for the lead from off the rail and gave way through the final sixteenth. FINE POINT ASSAY lacked early speed, raced four-wide through the turn angled in with a furlong to go and again nearing the sixteenth pole and finished evenly. TED'S CANDY GIRL was never far back, angled out in mid-stretch and gave way in the drive. VALDINI was off slow, showed no early speed, raced three-wide through the turn, angled in with a furlong to run, steadied and lost chance. GRANDIOSE SUMMER disputed the pace while racing four-wide and gave way after going a half. FULL OF WINE showed brief speed and weakened. THE STEWARDS CONDUCTED AND INQUIRY CONCERNING THE STEADYING OF VALDINI IN MID-STRETCH AND AFTER REVIEWNG THE FILMS CONCLUDED THAT BOTH TED'S CANDY GIRL HAD DRIFTED OUT AND FINE POINT ASSAY HAD DRIFTED IN TO CAUSE THE INFRACTIION AND DISQUALIFIED TED'S CANDY GIRL TO SIXTH AND FINE POINT ASSAY TO FIFTH. THE RACE WAS HAND TIMED. SOME TIMES CHANGED UPON REVIEW.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TURF PARADISE RACE 5 1M Dirt CR: 89. Claiming Purse 12400. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since February 15 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $8,500. Arizona Bred Claiming Price $10,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GIVE EM HECK BECK was away in good order to stalk the leaders while racing three-wide, moved up to take command nearing the three-eighths marker, opened a clear margin and held off the closing BARNFIELD to prevail. BARNFIELD lacked early speed, saved ground through the second turn, angled out into the stretch and was gaining on the winner late. MONGOL ALTAI was reserved just off the leaders early, moved three-wide through the second turn and rallied late. EXECUTIVE ACTION was forwardly placed early, moved four-wide through the second turn and lacked the needed late response. OUR VALLEY sprinted clear at once, saved ground while setting the pace and gave way after going five furlongs. FRISCO KID was void of early speed, raced off the rail through the second turn and was not a factor. IN THE MIDST was never far back, raced four-wide through the second turn and weakened. FORGOTTEN VOWS lagged early, moved three-wide through the second turn and did not offer a bid. THE RACE WAS HAND TIMED. SOME TIMES CHANGED UPON REVIEW.
